# House Price Prediction – Project Summary

## Overview

This project focuses on predicting house prices using Machine Learning techniques. The objective was to analyze housing data, identify the factors that influence property prices, and build predictive models capable of estimating house values accurately.

## Data Exploration and Cleaning

The dataset was loaded using Pandas and explored to understand its structure, features, and target variable. Missing values and duplicate records were checked and handled appropriately. Categorical features such as main road access, guest room availability, basement, air conditioning, and furnishing status were converted into numerical format using one-hot encoding to make them suitable for machine learning algorithms.

## Model Development

The dataset was divided into training and testing sets using an 80:20 split. Two regression models were implemented:

1. Linear Regression
2. Random Forest Regressor

Both models were trained on the processed dataset and evaluated using Mean Absolute Error (MAE), Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE), and R² Score.

## Visualization

Several visualizations were created to better understand the dataset and model performance:

* House Price Distribution Histogram
* Correlation Heatmap
* Actual vs Predicted House Price Scatter Plot

These charts helped identify relationships between features and evaluate prediction accuracy.

## Key Insights

The analysis revealed that factors such as property area, number of bathrooms, air conditioning, preferred location, and furnishing status significantly influence house prices. The Random Forest Regressor performed better than Linear Regression, indicating its ability to capture more complex relationships within the dataset.

## Conclusion

This project demonstrates the complete machine learning workflow, including data preprocessing, feature engineering, model training, evaluation, and visualization. The results show that machine learning can effectively assist in estimating property values and support data-driven decision-making in the real estate industry.
